cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the challenges of training machine learning models on distributed mobile devices, which involves distributed computing and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the implementation of gradient descent for logistic regression and SVM, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of mobile devices and the need for efficient communication also suggest the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with uncertainty and the need for fault tolerance, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of encoding strategies, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
